Depending on the business, changes are typically performed outside office hours to ensure no outages of required business resouces occur, especially during business hours.

Changes are performed via a automation or ticketing system, levels of automation differ greatly, meaning that changes can be performed with a click of a gui button or it will require hands on terminal usage or on-site presence.

Regardless, the change manager typically handles the processes in place and it is very common for the change manager to head a change meeting with required persons weekly/monthly/bi-monthly/tri-monthly so fourth, it all depends on busy-ness overall.
